Class NetworkNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.philips.cdp.dicommclient.networknode.NetworkNode
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    android.os.Parcelable

    public class NetworkNode
extends Object
implements android.os.Parcelable
    A network node represents an appliance that was found by discovery.

    It contains all the data that will be persisted.

      • useLegacyHttp

        public void useLegacyHttp()
        Indicate that the Appliance belonging to this NetworkNode only supports legacy HTTP connections over lan.

        If the appliance belonging to this NetworkNode supports HTTPS you should NOT call this, ever. As legacy HTTP is a deprecated technology within diComm, this is only here to support older devices which have not (or cannot) be updated to use HTTPS.
